
Jazz Semiconductor userware  - Information on Hdla netlister
_______________________________________________________________

The Hdla netlister generates .cir file which contains 'y' instances only.
When running Hdla netlister in 'template' mode, the Hdla netlister generates
both .cir file and .mtemp files.

______________________________________________________
instantiating hdla models in Eldo netlists (.cir file)
______________________________________________________

'hdla_' attributes are defined to control hdla model instantiations

When running Hdla netlister, attributes which begin with the prefix 'hdla_'
are used to control the instantiation of externally compiled hdla models. 

the 'hdla_model' attribute

If an attribute with the name 'hdla_model' is assigned to a cell instantiation 
with a value which begins with a letter, that instantiation is included in the 
Eldo netlist as an instantiation of a hdla model. If the value of hdla_model 
starts with any non alphabetic character, the value is assumed to be commented 
and it is ignored. A null or ignored value causes the instance to be ignored. 
The value should be of the form 'entity(architecture).' 

the 'hdla_coupling' attribute

The value of the attribute named 'hdla_coupling' is copied to an Eldo netlist 
hdla model instantiation as the contents of the "coupling:" list in the instantiation. 
It should be of the format of that list: instance_name_1->variable1 
instance_name_2->variable2.... 

other 'hdla_' attributes

Any other attribute which is given a name beginning with 'hdla_' is output in 
the hdla model instantiation's 'generic' list as a name=value pair. The 'hdla_' 
prefix is stripped from the name before output. 

controlling pin and port lists from Composer

Separation of Composer Connectors into Hdla pin and port lists and controlling the 
order of pins and ports at hdla model instantiation is done through the Composer 
'pin attribute' command. Pin attributes are assigned within the schematic of a
subcircuit for which an hdla model is to be substituted. If there is no schematic, 
a dummy schematic needs to be created with connectors for the block's signal i/o 
and its icon to be used at the parent level. A pin attribute with the name 'eldo' 
and the value 'pin N' or 'port N' needs to be defined on each pin. 'N' in the 
attribute value is the position in the pin or port map of each signal in the 
hdla model's pin or port definition statements. For instance, the signal which 
is to appear first in the pin connection list at instantiation should be given 
a pin attribute with the name 'eldo' and the value 'pin 1.' This mechanism allows
independent control of port and pin order irregardless of the state of the model source.
 
_______________________________________
hdla attributes at cell level
_______________________________________
The cell level attributes can be specified in CDF file in BASE mode.
 
_______________________________________
The Cadence batch mode netlisters:
_______________________________________

usage: nlhdla cellname libname       #for HDLA
usage: nlhdlat cellname libname      #for HDLA  (template)


Note: The nelisters need to be invoked from the directory in which you invoke Cadence system.
      libname can be ignored if your libname is ${PROJ_ID}_${LOGNAME}
      eg: ch25akit_test5 when login as test5 for ch25akit project.
      No Composer license is needed for using batch mode netlisters.

_______________________________________
output directory
_______________________________________
If environment variable HDLA_DIR is set, the .cir and .mtemp files are 
generated in the directory specified by HDLA_DIR. Otherwise, the .cir and 
.mtemp files are generated in the current directory.
